  "text": "In this respect, Kraidy's (2002:317) view on 'hybridity' as \"a communicative practice constitutive of, and constituted by, sociopolitical and economic arrangements\", is more helpful in understanding the complexity of local audience's reception of global media. [CITATION_1] important work on cultural hybridity in among Korean media industries, shows that cultural hybridity, is not simply an act of cultural democracy where the local appropriated global cultures.",
